The paper deals with graph representation on a grid and approximation algorithms for two classic graph problems, Maximum Independent Set and Minimum Dominating Set. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). However, since the paper focuses on graph problems and their approximation algorithms, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of grid-based graph representations also suggests cs.CG as a likely sub-category. The study of approximation algorithms for classic graph problems suggests cs.DS and cs.CC as likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of graph theory and combinatorics suggests cs.DM and cs.GT as possible sub-categories.
